Money is legal tendor (Mill, Pol. Econ. 12, 7). Legal· tender is that which must be tendered by the debtor and accepted by the creditor in discharge of a debt; a. g. in England silver coin is a legal tender only to the amount of forty shillings in any one payment, bronze coins are a legal tender only to the aggregate amount of one shilling.
